channel.title: Some Help, I dont wanna ruin this up
channel.description:
So currently I am putting my server online, I got the client running, i am using my no-ip for this server so what do I all change.
First I changed this one from runefx the orig server to my no-ip. (client.java) [img]http://i51.tinypic.com/24vqgeb.png[/img]
Once changed I go down to the other no-ip's what do I do with these? (client.java) [img]http://i51.tinypic.com/10fyrr5.png[/img]
Ok last thing the gui, what do I do in this folder? I found 0.0.0.0 keep it the same? or what. [img]http://i56.tinypic.com/4t0nyq.png[/img]
Please reply like,
#1 you do this #2 you do that blablabla
Thanks,
Barrick

item.title: Some Help, I dont wanna ruin this up
item.dc:creator: @arham_4 arham 4
item.description:
@arham_4 wrote:

[quote=“x1 att ftw x, post:2, topic:386336”]you did part 1 right and part to where it says // means that it is canceling the ip so what you do take the “//” out and replace the ip with your own

part 3 just leve it the same[/quote]
Why cancel a cancel? Just leave it and when you are logging in see if it’s saying logging in project-62.no-ip.org, rune-dynasty.no-ip.org, theparadiseowns.no-ip.org, or 0.0.0.0. If it does for example say connecting to rune-dynasty.no-ip.org then change that in client java to your ip. If it says logging in theparadiseowns.no-ip.org the replace that with you ip. If it says logging in 0.0.0.0 then replace 0.0.0.0 to your ip.
